
[1]frigidity

   FRIGID'ITY, n.

   1. Coldness; want of warmth. But not applied to the air or weather.

   2. Want of natural heat, life and vigor of body; impotency; imbecility;
   as the frigidity of old age.

   3. Coldness of affection.

   4. Dullness; want of animation or intellectual fire; as the frigidity
   of sentiments or style.
